                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "text": "Provide students with a foundational understanding of how air interacts with solid objects, a concept crucial for fields like aerospace engineering, automotive design, and environmental engineering. Key topics:",
                            "style": []
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "text": "Fundamentals of Fluid Mechanics",
                            "style": [
                                "bold"
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "text": ": Introduction to the properties of fluids, the concept of pressure, buoyancy, and flow patterns.",
                            "style": []
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "text": "Aerodynamic Forces",
                            "style": [
                                "bold"
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "text": ": Understanding lift, drag, and thrust, including how these forces affect the performance and design of vehicles and structures.",
                            "style": []
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "text": "Airflow Dynamics",
                            "style": [
                                "bold"
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "text": ": Study of laminar and turbulent flow, boundary layers, and the impact of these factors on aerodynamic efficiency.",
                            "style": []
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "text": "Theory and Application",
                            "style": [
                                "bold"
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "text": ": Introduction to Bernoulli\u2019s equation and other aerodynamic theories, with applications to aircraft, cars, bridges, and buildings.",
                            "style": []
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "text": "Wind Tunnel Testing",
                            "style": [
                                "bold"
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "text": ": Basics of wind tunnel testing, including scale modeling and data analysis techniques used in aerodynamic design.",
                            "style": []
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "text": "Computational Fluid Dynamics (CFD)",
                            "style": [
                                "bold"
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "text": ": An overview of how CFD is used in predicting and analyzing aerodynamic properties in complex scenarios.",
                            "style": []
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "text": "Prerequisite: None",
                            "style": [
                                "italic"
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
